All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.Observer, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.Scrollable
public class JSimMainWindowList
extends javax.swing.JList
implements java.util.Observer

A JSimMainWindowList is a list whose items are simple descriptions of processes, queues, or other simulation elements. The elements must implement JSimDisplayable.

Since:
J-Sim version 0.1.2
Version:
J-Sim version 0.6.0
Author:
Pavel DOMECKÝ, Jarda KAČER

Constant Field Values

logger

private static final java.util.logging.Logger logger
Common logger for all instances of this class. By default, all logging information goes to a file. Only severe events go to the console, in addition to a file.

myParent

private JSimSimulation myParent
The simulation that this list's main window belongs to.

objectsToDisplay

private java.util.Set<? extends JSimDisplayable> objectsToDisplay
A set of objects delivered by the simulation that this list has to display. If the set is ordered, the list will also be ordered.

myInfoTable

private java.util.ArrayList<JSimDisplayable> myInfoTable
An array list of displayed objects. A selected item's position is used as an index to this array list.

update

Updates the items in the list if the state of displayed objects has changed since last call of update().

Specified by:
update in interface java.util.Observer

getInfoTable

protected java.util.ArrayList<JSimDisplayable> getInfoTable()
Return a table of all items displayed in the list. It is important to provide such an ordered list because the main window will access the displayed objects via their indices when a double-click occurs.

Returns:
An array list containing all displayed objects in the same order that they are displayed.
